[SN]TITLE[SN]
Taylor Swift announces UK dates in June 2015

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Taylor Swift has announced she'll play three UK concerts next year.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
She will perform in Glasgow, Manchester and London in June and is part of her world tour that takes in North America, Europe and ends in Australia.
It's been a big few months for the American singer, 1989, her fifth studio album has reached number one in the UK.
taylorswift.com
The record is the fastest-selling album of the year by a female artist and it sold more than 90,000 copies in the past week.
The 24-year-old will be joined on part of the tour by Vance Joy. Last month she covered his song Riptide in the Radio 1 Live Lounge.
She has career record sales in excess of 30 million albums and almost 80 million song downloads, which makes her one of the top five selling digital music artists in the world.
It's not known who will support her in the UK.
Tickets for the Glasgow and Manchester shows will go on sale on Friday 7 November and tickets for British Summer Time Hyde Park are available on Monday 10 November.
